    <text>
        <body>
            <div><opener><salute><persName ref="pe2111">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Owen</persName></salute></opener>
                
                <p>I thank you for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> note &amp; shall be glad to receive the sequel of 
                    y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> enquir<gap reason="illegible" unit="letters" quantity="1"/>ies. 
                    I find so much time lost by sending the sheets thro’ y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> hands, that I 
                    shall not trouble you except on difficulties.</p>
                
                <p>I shall be obliged to you for calling on <persName ref="pe0424">m<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sherwin</persName> engraver 
                    in <placeName ref="pl3036">Bond street</placeName> for my <rs type="art" ref="ar0458">print of M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pitt</rs>.  
                    I left money to pay my 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> subscription but as <sic>the</sic> has left town, I must request 
                    <persName ref="pe0328">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Faulder</persName> to pay you the ½ Guinea for that purpose. I wish you would wrap it 
                    carefully with soft paper round a Roller &amp; leave it at <persName ref="pe0111">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Hughes</persName>’s 
                    No 8 or 10 <placeName ref="pl3037">John street adelphi</placeName><note type="editorial">Pennant probably refers to his printer, 
                        Henry Hughs (or Hughes), although no record associating him with an address at John Street, Adelphi, has been identified, and the spelling 
                        of the name ('Hughes') is uncharacteristic of Pennant.</note> who will bring it down.
                </p>
                
                <closer><salute>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> friend
                </salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Th. Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="0001">Downing</placeName> July 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1789.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            
            <div>
                
                <p><address><addrLine><persName ref="pe2111">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> William Owen</persName>.
                    </addrLine></address></p>
            </div>
        </body>
